The EPD may also include other relevant social and economic information as additional and voluntary information. This may be product information or a description of an organisationâs overall work on
social or economic sustainability, such as activities related to supply chain management or social responsibility.
Any additional social and economic information declared shall be substantiated and verifiable, and be derived using appropriate methods and be specific, accurate, not misleading, and relevant to the specific product. Quantitative information is preferred over qualitative information.
Further information on which indicators that could be used can be obtained by the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) documents
.
